<item>
            <title>[LU-10337] Open by handle does not work with unlinked files from multiple nodes</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10337</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When doing open by handle, a requirement is that it be possible to open already open unlinked files. This is important for the sort of userspace NFS server/ i/o forwarder (DVS) uses that file handles are intended for.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This works from one node in Lustre, but not across multiple nodes. This looks fixable - It&apos;s possible to open an orphaned file, it seems to be as simple as using the code from mdd_close in mdd_open, particularly rewriting the &quot;EEXIST check&quot; (mdd_is_dead_obj) to check if the object is an orphan and then open it anyway.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch forthcoming.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
